lign=left class=m><span class=title> Rules of exp camping.</span><hr size=1> Exp camping is defined as killing the same mob/mobs over and over again for the sole purpose of gaining lvls. Loot is always nice, but not a requirement. (the Ph4t L3wtz are all 46+ anyway(or something like that))<br>
<br>
Here are a few rules of camping.<br>
<br>
1. Don't bother taking out whites/yellows/reds. Too much effort for deminished returns.<br>
<br>
2. Static spawns are best. No searching, set your timer, heh.<br>
<br>
3. If solo go for 2 low blues. If group go for more. (sister isle lvl 25 npc for example)<br>
<br>
4. Find a safe spot to sit/med.  If you have to worry about stuff attacking you, move.  <br>
<br>
5. Find something else to do.  don't sit there and watch you mana/hp go up.  Read a book, do your chores. <br>
<br>
6. Be prepared to get bored. You are killin the same thing over and over and over again. Hence taking along a friend or five if possible, talk about junk.  learn to say /gu LARS McMANUS IS A SON OF A BEECH!!!(if you have to know give me a /tell)<br>
<br>
7. DO NOT EVER INVOKE PNP!!!  If they guy there is getting exp, leave. Ask if you can be put on a list or something. Who cares if he/she can get better loot/exp somewhere else. Only invoke play nice policy on spawns if that person is not going to get exp.  Respect other peoples camp, and they will respect yours. Don't be &quot;that guy.&quot;<br>
<br>
8. If something completely kicks your butt, try something different. Either a new stratagy or something. Don't give up on first try.<br>
<br>
9. Remember to bind near.  If the fit hits the shan you don't want to be accross the world.<br>
<br>
10. Before you leave get your bubble of experience cushion. Bub and half after hell levels. You don't want to lose your hard earned lvls.<br>
<br>
11. Most importantly.  try to have fun. <br>
<br>
If you feel like you are going to pull all your hair out if you kill soandso one more time.  Stop.  Go do something else.  If you have killed enough, you can probalby do something you couldn't before.<br>
<br>
It sure does feel good to walk through a dungeon you used to be kos in, and not be touched, because all the mobs are crapping their pants hoping you don't kill them.<br>
